Architecture plan

Project shape:
- Vite + React + TypeScript single-page clock app.
- Runtime code lives under `src/`, with React composition currently in `src/main.tsx`.
- Shared deterministic date/time helpers live under `src/lib/` and are covered by Vitest.
- Browser integration coverage lives under `e2e/` and runs against the production preview path.

Module structure and file organization:
- `src/main.tsx`: current app composition and React root mounting. Issue #29 should lift the ticking `Date` state here so the analog and digital clocks share the same timestamp.
- `src/components/Clock.tsx`: digital clock display. Today it owns its own interval; Issue #29 should adjust it to render from the shared date state instead of ticking independently.
- `src/components/FormatToggle.tsx`: controlled 12h/24h toggle.
- `src/components/AnalogClock.tsx`: planned SVG component for Issue #28. It should render the circular dial, 60 tick marks, Roman outer numerals, Arabic inner numerals, and three rotated line hands.
- `src/hooks/useHourFormat.ts`: persisted hour-format preference.
- `src/lib/formatTime.ts`: pure string formatting helper.
- `src/lib/getHandAngles.ts`: pure analog-clock helper returning `{ hour, minute, second }` degrees.
- `src/lib/getHandAngles.test.ts`: existing tests, to be expanded by Issue #27 with the requested edge and interpolation cases.
- `e2e/clock.spec.ts`: existing Playwright coverage, to be extended by Issue #30 after analog integration.

Shared types and contracts:
- `getHandAngles(date: Date): { hour: number; minute: number; second: number }`.
- Angles are degrees clockwise from 12 o'clock.
- Second hand: `seconds * 6`.
- Minute hand: `(minutes + seconds / 60) * 6`, so it moves smoothly as seconds pass.
- Hour hand: `(hours % 12 + minutes / 60) * 30`, so it moves smoothly as minutes pass.
- `AnalogClock` should receive a `date: Date` prop and derive hand angles via `getHandAngles`; it should not own timers or persistence.
- The integrated app should maintain one per-second `Date` state shared by `AnalogClock` and `Clock`.

Issue dependencies:
- #27 depends on the existing hand-angle helper and can be implemented first by expanding `src/lib/getHandAngles.test.ts`.
- #28 depends on the helper and base styling; implement `AnalogClock` as a reusable controlled visual component.
- #29 depends on #28 and the existing wired digital clock/toggle layout; it integrates `AnalogClock` and lifts the ticking date state.
- #30 depends on #29; update Playwright only after the analog SVG is visible in the real app.

Key design decisions:
- Keep angle calculation pure and independent of React, DOM APIs, timers, and localStorage.
- Keep `AnalogClock` presentational and driven by props so tests and future layouts can reuse it.
- Prefer SVG elements with accessible labels/testable structure over canvas so E2E can assert circles, hands, and numerals directly.
- Use CSS transforms with `transform-origin: center` for hand rotation, with stable hand identifiers/classes for Playwright assertions.
- Preserve the current dark theme and responsive centered layout; avoid introducing new state beyond the single shared `Date`.
